ata-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_7279245\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 28, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yra1718699884457.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yra1718699884457.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yra1718699884457.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nnl1665702895680\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      SSP Paths and Connection\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Components are assigned to stored procedures using assignment files. All stored procedure components which have the default Stored Procedure Component implementation type are mapped to the <code class=\"ph codeph\">$SSP</code> path.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nnl1665702895680__p_d36281e1_d36282e1_d36283e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$SSP</code> can point to a separate or shared DBMS connection. You must explicitly map the <code class=\"ph codeph\">$SSP</code> path, because it has no default mapping. Stored procedure components can also be mapped to an explicit DBMS connection, via the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ujx1665702543107.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujx1665702543107.html\" title=\"Use the [SERVICES_EXEC] section of the assignment file to direct the execution of service components to a network path, COM, or SOAP connector, and to redefine the behavior of COM and SOAP connectors for specific components.\">[SERVICES_EXEC]</a> section. Stored procedure components can also be located on a remote DBMS, and accessed via a Uniface Server.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nnl1665702895680__p_d36284e1_d36285e1_d36286e1\">If a component has multiple implementations (including a stored procedure component which is not set to default), explicitly assigning the component to a DBMS connection in the [SERVICES_EXEC] section results in Uniface using the Stored Procedure Component implementation.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nnl1665702895680__p_d36287e1_d36288e1_d36289e1\">Uniface ensures that a DBMS connection is established before a stored procedure component operation executes the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> ProcScript statement.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nnl1665702895680__section_sjk_gbc_fcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle exampletitle\" id=\"nnl1665702895680__p_d36290e1_d36291e1_d36292e1\">Example: Mapping Stored\n            Procedure Components to a Connection</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nnl1665702895680__p_d36293e1_d36294e1_d36295e1\">All stored procedure components are mapped to the\n            $ORA2 (via $SSP) connection, with the exception of component_1, which is mapped to the\n            $ORA1 connection.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"nnl1665702895680__pre_vjk_gbc_fcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[PATHS]\n$ORA1 =ORA:|scott|tiger\n$ORA2 =ORA:|system|manager\n$SSP =$ORA2\n[SERVICES_EXEC]\ncomponent_1 = $ORA1:component_1\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7279245\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7279245\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "SSP Paths and Connection Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 28, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 SSP Paths and Connection Components are assigned to stored procedures using assignment files. All stored procedure components which have the default Stored Procedure Component implementation type are mapped to the $SSP path. $SSP can point to a separate or shared DBMS connection. You must explicitly map the $SSP path, because it has no default mapping. Stored procedure components can also be mapped to an explicit DBMS connection, via the [SERVICES_EXEC] section. Stored procedure components can also be located on a remote DBMS, and accessed via a Uniface Server. If a component has multiple implementations (including a stored procedure component which is not set to default), explicitly assigning the component to a DBMS connection in the [SERVICES_EXEC] section results in Uniface using the Stored Procedure Component implementation. Uniface ensures that a DBMS connection is established before a stored procedure component operation executes the activate ProcScript statement. Example: Mapping Stored Procedure Components to a Connection All stored procedure components are mapped to the $ORA2 (via $SSP) connection, with the exception of component_1, which is mapped to the $ORA1 connection. [PATHS] $ORA1 =ORA:|scott|tiger $ORA2 =ORA:|system|manager $SSP =$ORA2 [SERVICES_EXEC] component_1 = $ORA1:component_1 Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}